<section id="support-main" class="support page navigable text">
  <section class="container">
    <h6><a href="../support">&larr; Svbtle support</a></h6>
    <h1 class="">Using a custom domain</h1>

    <p>To set up a custom domain with Svbtle, you need to create special records at your DNS provider. Svbtle only supports A-records.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><p><strong>If you&rsquo;re using a subdomain, like <em>blog.yourdomain.com</em></strong>, create a single A-record at your DNS provider for <em>blog.yourdomain.com</em> that points to <code>107.20.198.228</code></p></li>
      <li><p><strong>If you&rsquo;re using a naked domain, like <em>yourdomain.com</em></strong>, create two A-records at your DNS provider: one for <em>www.yourdomain.com</em> and another for <em>yourdomain.com</em>. Both should point to <code>107.20.198.228</code></p>
    </ul>

    <p>The exact method for creating A-records differs depending on your domain registrar and/or DNS service.</p>

    <p>Once you&rsquo;ve created the correct DNS records, it may take up to twenty-four hours to take effect. When your DNS settings have taken effect, log in to Svbtle and add your domain to the <a href="../settings/blog">Blog section of Settings</a>. Type only &ldquo;yourdomain.com&rdquo; or &ldquo;blog.yourdomain.com&rdquo; (don’t add &ldquo;www.&rdquo; or &ldquo;http://&rdquo;) in the &ldquo;custom domain&rdquo; box.</p>

    <hr/>

    <p>If you&rsquo;d like <code>HTTPS</code> support, which is in beta, please <a href="mailto:hello@svbtle.com?subject=HTTPS">email us</a> and we we&rsquo;ll enable it for you.</p>

    <p>If you need more help, send us an email: <a href="mailto:hello@svbtle.com?subject=Custom%20domain%20help" class="">hello@svbtle.com</a>.</p>

    <hr>

    <a href="../support" class="harsh tiny">Back to support</a>
  </section>
